Elliotte,

Sometimes I would just trust that System.exit does what it says, and 
leave the little method untested.  I&#39;d do this most often in exception 
handling code, where I don&#39;t have strong customer input about the right 
thing to do, but still want to have defined behavior.

On the other hand, if adding the exit was because of an explicit 
customer request or bug report, I&#39;d probably add a shell script to my 
system (&quot;customer&quot;) tests, outside of JUnit, to make sure that I&#39;d 
captured the bug and the fix.  I haven&#39;t done this for System.exit yet, 
but I have for other behavior only observable from the command line.

    David Saff

